profile.title: Visualizer/Filter 2.0.2 15 in 18 1:4-5
profile.author: Decent
profile.notes:
A new technique developed by Scott Rao, for making filter coffee with a espresso machine and 24g basket.  The process: (1) insert two micron 55mm paper filter into the bottom of a clean portafilter basket.  (2) Rinser the filter and basket with hot water.  (3) Fill the basket with 20g to 22g of finely ground coffee, not quite espresso grind, but far finer than any filter grind.  (4) WDT the grounds.  (5) tamping is optional.  (6) Place a metal mesh filter on top.  (7) Lock in the portafilter and make the espresso to a 5:1 ratio.

bean.notes:
- This is our very first Java from Takesi and we can honestly say this java is the best Java washed we've ever tasted! Very delicate yet fruity coffee with the cultivar's iconic notes of green tea.
- Takesi Java delivers delicious fruit flavors that reminds us of nectarine, balanced out by meadow honey sweetness and vibrant green tea notes throughout.
